pokemondemo

Features
Card Listing: Browse through a collection of Pokémon cards with animated transitions.
Card Details: View detailed information about individual cards, including their types, HP, attacks, weaknesses, and more.
Like (Save) Cards: Save or remove cards to/from your favorites list.
Animated Header: Experience a dynamic header that collapses on scrolling.
Dark/Light Theme Support: Automatically adapts to the device's color scheme.

Frontend: React Native, Expo
Navigation: Expo Router
State Management: Context API
Animations: Reanimated 2
Custom Components: Themed UI components for consistency
Installation
Follow these steps to run the project locally:

Prerequisites
Node.js (v14 or higher)
Expo CLI
A Pokémon card API or local card data in contexts/pokemonContext
Steps
Clone this repository:

git clone https://github.com/ArifDKNT/pokemondemo.git / (or Download Zip)
cd pokemondemo
Install dependencies:
npm/bun/yarn install
Start the development server:
npm/bun/yarn start
Use the Expo Go app on your device or an emulator to preview the app.

Usage
Open the app.
Browse the Pokémon cards on the home screen.
Tap a card to view its details.
Save or remove the card from your favorites using the heart button.
Navigate back to the main screen or explore more cards.
